CH12

These things are not new, but ancient; they have been made new in you. For this is the eternal Word, who was from the beginning, who is now made known, and who is to come. This is the one through whom the Father created all things.
For what else could hide the counsel of God except His own beloved Son? By whom He made all things and through whom He revealed the mysteries of truth.
This is the tree of knowledge and the tree of life. Whoever eats of it shall live forever. This is the knowledge of the Father, which is immortal.
The soul is immortal and lives forever. The flesh is mortal and can be destroyed. But God has united the immortal soul with the mortal flesh, so that through the resurrection He might display His power.
For God loved mankind, for whose sake He made the world, to whom He gave all things, to whom He promised the kingdom of heaven.
This is the knowledge of the truth, which the Word taught, which the Father revealed through the Son.
The soul dwells in the body as the Church dwells in the world. The soul loves the body that hates it. So the Church loves those who hate her.

